{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The content passed to summary generation includes data from metrics, issue tracker, and deployment log.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: the failure boundary is the handoff between multiple modules (three collectors -> aggregator -> summary step), not one pure function. REAL-INFRA: behavior text does not require real network/OS; source clients can be in-process stubs. MOCK-HIDE: a unit test of only one mapper could miss missing-source wiring, but an integration test with three wired collectors catches it. LLM-DEP: this checks input payload to summary step, not model output quality, so Agentic is disqualified by behavior text ('content passed to the summary-generation step'). MULTI-STEP: no multi-agent pipeline described, so Workflow is disqualified.","test_description":"Wire real collection/orchestration modules with stubbed source adapters returning distinct fixture payloads; replace summary generator with a spy. Execute one report run and assert the exact summary-input object contains all three source sections with expected key fields.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.17,"Integration":0.78,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"If one source is unavailable, the report is still produced with a 'data unavailable' note for that section.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: this is cross-module error propagation (collector failure -> report composer fallback note) so Unit is too low. REAL-INFRA: behavior says 'one data source is unavailable' but does not require validating real timeout/socket semantics; in-process failure injection is sufficient. REJECTION-GATE for System: no explicit text about real HTTP timeout/load/OS behavior. LLM-DEP: correctness here is fallback handling, not model judgment quality. MULTI-STEP: no chained agentic decisions.","test_description":"Run orchestration with two source stubs returning data and one source stub raising an unavailability error. Assert run does not abort, output report is generated, and the failed section contains the exact 'data unavailable' marker.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.07,"Integration":0.65,"System":0.15,"Agentic":0.12,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"Narrative summary accurately represents key values in input data.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"LLM-DEP: behavior explicitly tests summary accuracy/faithfulness, which depends on what the real summary model produces; deterministic stubs would always pass and hide hallucination/misstatement failures. REJECTION-GATE for Integration: disqualified by behavior text 'accurately represents' (output-quality requirement). MULTI-STEP: only one model decision point is required here, so Workflow is disqualified.","test_description":"Use a fixed dataset with known key values and call the real summary-generation model. Score output against required factual checks (all required values present, no contradictory values). Run multiple trials to account for non-determinism and fail if factual error rate exceeds threshold.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.03,"Integration":0.3,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.62,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"End-to-end report flow reaches the configured recipient inbox correctly.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"REAL-INFRA: this requires real external email delivery/inbox behavior and networked integration; in-process fakes cannot prove inbox receipt. MOCK-HIDE: mocked mail clients can pass while real SMTP/API auth, routing, or delivery issues fail. REJECTION-GATE for Agentic: behavior text is delivery success ('reaches inbox correctly'), not model-output quality. REJECTION-GATE for Workflow: no requirement for multiple agentic decision stages.","test_description":"Execute the